.SH NAME
dotty-security-key-disallow - Remove security keys from a profile's allowlist.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty security-key disallow [|\&...] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Remove security keys from a profile's allowlist (the active profile unless
--profile names another). Removing the last entry lifts the restriction —
the profile allows every key again.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for disallow


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)

.PP
\fB--serial\fP=""
	serial number of the security key


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty security-key disallow
  dotty --profile=work security-key disallow 12345678
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty-security-key(1)\fP
